body:
@samaujs The account your Rinkeby Eth are being swept to also [exists on mainnet](https://etherscan.io/address/0x7097f41f1c1847d52407c629d0e0ae0fdd24fd58) with a balance of ~60 ETH. There's a single comment which says: `hi man! are you a cool crowler?`.  

If you have a chance could you open an issue at `go-ethereum` [here](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues) and provide the same information you've provided in this issue?  They might have a clearer sense of what's going on. 

In the interim I would not ~~use any addresses generated by~~ your local geth client for any real transactions [edit: with your current settings]
